- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with the combinatorial complexity of the convex hull of a set of spheres in $\mathbb{E}^d$, and also reduces the problem to the convex hull of a set of convex polytopes lying on parallel hyperplanes. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely, as the paper involves combinatorial analysis of the worst-case complexity of the convex hull problem. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category, as the paper deals with the geometry of spheres and convex polytopes, and their convex hulls. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category, as the paper discusses algorithmic considerations and tight bounds for the convex hull problem. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper involves mathematical analysis and computation of the worst-case complexity of the convex hull problem.
